15. data()
-----------

Returns pointer to underlying array.

Example:

int* ptr = arr.data();

Useful when passing data to C APIs.

Interview Q:
Why does std::array provide data()?

Answer:
Because elements are stored contiguously and can be exposed as a raw pointer.

